Text: \\<sob> \\<sniffle>
Help me... Somebody...
Yeowch! I-I don't want to become porxelain!
Eeek!
Nooo! The water will warp my winsome curves!
Ack! Burst this bubble, will you!
He must...be stopped...
Damn you... Gaius...
N-Not me, silly! The nightmare!
Just so! Empower me with your hatred, your despair!
Curse you, Father! You sent him to his death!
Savages! You stole him from me!
Brother, do not leave me, I beg you!
Bradamante... First Brother, then you...
My life for vengeance!
It won't end like thisss!
What surprise is in store for us next, I wonder.
I trust you'll make the right choice this time.
I will defer to your judgment.
The choice is clear.
Whatever comes out, we can handle it.
I tire of this guardian's games.
Go on. Trust your instincts.
Soon we can quit this place.
Well done.
My thanks.
Thank goodness...
Wha...what happened?
Thank you.
Right!
Draw their attention from Cymet!
We have to hold on!
Stand back!
Spread out!
There are so many!
Quickly, before they can overwhelm us!
That should be the last of the chamber's defenses.
At last we can leave.
I am glad that is over...
Hmmm...
Hmmm...
The site of the Bozja incident...
(Did it appear because he mentioned the Principia, I wonder?)
Someone help!
Stay back!
Raaagh!
Down with the Empire!
For Bozja!
Damn you!
Filthy savages!
Down with you!
Steady, men!
Open fire!
I want those savages found!
Last chance to surrender!
I say we strike before they can regroup.
Why bother? They're but ants beneath our boot.
You know the price for insurrection!
No, please!
Get...
...Out.
Father was so angry that day...
Raaaaaargh!
Hurry...!
I can't...hold it...!
On your knees!
Now I have you!
There is no escape!
What is the meaning of thisss?
Ow, that's my liver!
Betrayed!
Come unto flesh, O forgotten form...
\\<hiss>
Every last one of you will die!
Die, and lie beneath the silt!
The Dheema demands your head!
I regret to disappoint, but I'm more than comfortable with heights!
Ugh, the stench is unbearable!
If you have any complaints about the schedule, feel free to take them up with Master Wawalago.
Fish, you landlubbers, fish!

Would that I had brought my own rod... Perhaps if I...
Ah, what am I thinkin'? I've captainly duties to attend to!
The stronger the bite, the bigger the fish!
Fish might look simple, but some can be mighty particular when it comes to their bait.
Fish! Fish with every scantling of your being!
Fish twice as hard, for my sake!
Hah hah, the feast is here!
If you can't land a catch now, I'll have to ask you to turn in your rod!
Distraction's a fisher's worst enemy! Focus on your rod! Focus!
When the sun sets, the sea comes alive.
Once, one of my crew dropped a lantern overboard. The waters started glittering as if to thank us!
Rumor has it that during rough weather is when the spectral megalodon sets out on its hunt.
Pray you don't disturb the spectral megalodon. I've heard stories of it swallowin' whole crews in one gulp.
In the dead of night, I swear I've seen the coral itself movin' about like some kind of worm.
There ain't a shrimp to be found in these waters. What's eatin' them, you think?
The spectral discus is a sight to see, but it'll startle at the smallest sound.
Watch out for the spectral discus─it ain't tiny, so I reckon it'll be hard to miss!
What? Are those...mouse bones? What in the seven hells happened here?
If you're in the mood for a fright, try fishin' here in the dark. You won't regret it─or maybe you will!
This heat's rough, but if you can bear the sun beatin' down on you, you'll have your pick of the fish.
The fish here are huge, and slow as they come! Shouldn't be hard to land a catch.
Last time we made land someone told me of a fish that swims with the risin' sun.
I've seen some fishers have luck with a longer cast.
The fish here might be small, but they're as fierce as any in the sea!
When the wind howls and the thunder claps, the prize catches come out to swim.
They say when thunder rolls across the sky, it whips certain fish into a frenzy. So they say, anyway.
If you're lookin' to bait the spectral current, you'll want to cast for the little fish, I reckon.
Local legend has it that when night falls, a horror rises from the depths to drag down unwary vessels...
What's been eatin' the squid, then? This spot used to be swarmin' with 'em.
Bloody hells, it's comin' down in buckets. This'll rile up the schools...
Bait your hook for fish of middling size. You'll thank me later.
Saw an unlikely creature in the water earlier this morning─thought I might still be dreamin'.
Little insects are the ticket to some extraordinary catches. Trust me.
Ugh, it's like sailin' through a damn waterfall. Just the kind of weather they like to hunt in...
Careful, now. There's some big, mean buggers that swim in these parts, and they ain't shy about comin' up for a bite!
Sometimes after dusk, you hear it echo across the water...a grindin', crackin', crunchin' kind of sound.
I hear the beaches hereabouts are strewn with bits of shattered shells.
Some fish love swimmin' about in a thunderstorm. It's like they're just darin' a bolt to strike!
No one knows why, but big catches and spectral currents often go hand in hand. What's the ocean tellin' us, I wonder?
Around here the risin' sun brings big fish, lookin' for a meal. Wouldn't want to miss breakfast.
A master fisher once told me that he owed his success to the sack of fresh mackerel he always kept close at hand.
I can barely tell the sea from the rain! Those little buggers love swimmin' in a downpour, though...
Stands to reason that to catch a small fish, you need even smaller bait!
I've heard whispers that a pair of Ruby Dragons prowl these waters at night. Always wanted to see 'em with my own eyes.
Glass dragons aren't known to suffer competition. If you want to draw one out, make it think a rival's encroachin' on their territory.
Storm like this, I'd bet a sack o' gil that a certain fish is on the prowl...
Keep your wits about you in these waters. The fish might not look it, but they can pull that rod right out of your hands!
Sailors say that when night falls, you can see a volcano come to life on the ocean floor, like a single red eye openin' in the darkness.
Squid are a common sight around here, as are the things that come to hunt 'em.
Sometimes you have to get soakin' wet to have a chance at catchin' the best fish.
Brace yourselves against something sturdy. The big bastards in these waters like to give passin' boats a love tap from time to time.
Sailors passin' through these parts have told stories of an undersea flower bed in full bloom.
The plum trees are a sight to behold─if you can ignore the bugs swarmin' around them, that is.
Cluck cluck!
Cluck... Cluck! Cluck!
W-Wait...get back here!
\\<pant> \\<pant>
Chase down those birds and nab them in your nets!
Use birdlime to slow them down!
Be gentle with the birds, okay!?
These are some feisty chickens...
Thank you, friend! You're a lifesaver!
Please lend us your aid again!
How many more are still out there!?
Wait... I said wait!
Get back here already, will you!?
\\<pant> I've had enough...
Am I in the right place for the procession?
The eggs are ready. Let the festivities begin!
Heh. Today's smilin' children are tomorrow's loyal customers.
Can I take this godsdamned rabbit's pate off? It's godsdamned swelterin' in here!
It seems the gang's all here!
Are you ready, my friends? The parade is about to begin!
We make for the Lancers' Guild! Come one, come all!
And we're off!
Spriggans!? Why does it always have to be spriggans...
Show some spirit! It's Hatching–tide, after all!
Anythin' to drum up business...
What does a bloke have to do to get a bleedin' drink around here!?
Don't forget the children! Share the gift of Hatching–tide with one and all!
Over here! No child must go home empty-handed!
Our work here is done! Time to move on!
Prepare the presents! The children await!
I'm a weaponsmith, not a bleedin' wet nurse!
Spriggy spriggy! Eggs so pretty!
Spriggy say less talky, more givy!
Seven hells! What in the─!?
Alright, already! Just get your bloody paws off me!
I could swear I've heard that voice somewhere...
No, it couldn't be...
Mister Rabbit! Missus Rabbit! Do you have an egg for me!?
And me! I want an egg, too!
No dilly-dallying! We must move on!
The Lancers' Guild is up ahead. Just a bit further now!
The procession is almost at an end. How many children smiled because of you today?
We must drive them out!
There's only one thing these savages are good for...
Just getting started!
That I should lose again...
This marks the end of the procession!
Be proud, my friends, for you have made many a child happy this day!
Should you be willing to join us again, we welcome your participation.
Till next time, a happy Hatching–tide to one and all!
All right, people, it's time for our first concerted works in a while!
We're buildin' the Mattock, and to begin with, we need to clear away the debris!
It's the first of many steps to come, so let's see this off to a good start!
We've got the supplies we need. Now it's time to get to work!
It's the same task as before─clearing away debris in preparation for the road!
Let's see to it nothin' lies in the way of the reconstruction effort!
To your places, everyone. It's time to get to work!
Today, we're clearing away the last little bits of debris on the Mattock.
How good a job we do will tell on the next works, so let's make it squeaky clean!
Our stores are in good order, which means it's time for more concerted works!
Grab the supplies you need, and let's pave the way─literally and figuratively!
The end's in sight, so give it everything you've got!
All right! It's time for the next round of concerted works!
We're gettin' started on the fountain. Grab the supplies you need and put 'em to use!
This will be a place of rest and relaxation for residents, so let's not spare any effort!
I hope you're all ready to work, because today we're makin' that fountain flow!
Everything you need, you can get from the supply pile!
Let's make it into a beautiful place the residents can be proud of!
All right, everyone. From today, we're commencin' works on Saint Roelle's Dais!
First things first: we need scaffolds. Grab yourselves some supplies and get to it!
We're layin' the groundwork for what's to come, so let's make it as sturdy as can be!
Right then, it's time to get busy on Saint Roelle's Dais!
The area's a mess of debris, so that's what we're gonna work on today.
Let's put our backs into it and clear ourselves a path!
Get ready, everyone! It's time for another round of concerted works!
We're clearin' away the last bits of debris scattered across Saint Roelle's Dais.
Might be as it's a humble task, but let's do a tidy job of it!
We've reached our target for supplies. Time to get to work again!
Grab what you need from the supply pile, and we'll start fixin' up Saint Roelle's Dais!
Speed's of the essence for this task, so let's keep those hands movin'!
Right, it's time to make Saint Roelle's Dais true to its name!
Help yourselves to the supplies, and let's see the stage finished!
Show me the best of your workmanship, now!
All right, everyone, we're finally gettin' started on the New Nest proper!
First order of business is clearin' the debris in the area by the Mendicant's Court!
The more hands we have, the quicker we'll be done!
Roll up your sleeves, 'cause concerted works are startin'!
Today, we're clearin' away more debris ahead of construction on the New Nest!
Let's stay focused and get it done with the least fuss!
Right, the appointed hour's here. Let's get to work!
There's still debris in the New Nest that wants for clearin', so that's our task for today.
Once we're done, that'll be it for the large chunks!
Right, let's get these works underway!
This time we're clearin' away the fine debris still scattered about the New Nest.
There's a lot of ground to cover, so we'll want to split into smaller crews!
All right, everyone, it's time for more concerted works!
After all that clearin' we did for the New Nest, we're finally startin' on the actual buildin'.
Grab the supplies you need, and we'll fix up all the streets and steps!
Startin' from today, we're gonna be buildin' houses!
This hardly needs sayin', but this is what we've been workin' towards!
So go and grab some supplies, and let's show our builders' spirit!
To your places, everyone! We're commencin' concerted works!
Today, we're completin' the first set of houses! You know where the supplies are!
The work we do here will set the tone for the rest, so let your skills shine!
Our stores are in good shape. It's time to get back to it!
We're startin' on more houses today, and we'll keep buildin' them till we've filled up the New Nest.
Take what supplies you need and put 'em to good use!
We've replenished our supplies, so it's time for more works!
The goal today's to complete another set of houses.
Let's build 'em as if you're buildin' your own home!
Right, everyone, it's time to commence the next works!
This time it's the final site for the New Nest, and the last set of houses!
By now it goes without sayin', but the job calls for precision, so let's keep it nice and tidy!
This is it, everyone! The very last works for the New Nest!
Today, we're completin' not only the last of the houses, but the entire area as well!
Let's give it absolutely everything we've got and finish on a high note!
Deft of paw, with kin do I vie.
Betterment of the whole do our efforts descry.
With fearsome fang, I travel with pack.
For peace our land shall never lack.
On my belly do I crawl.
By my strength, prosperity reigns in our hall.
We must choose carefully.
Perhaps a hint is carved in the stone...
Hmmm...
Would that I could read these talismans.
\\<sigh> I can make no sense of this riddle.
Is there perhaps some meaning to their arrangement?
Strange... All of these talismans appear blank to my eye.
On your guard!
Finally.
Ah! What is that!?
Let us be brief.
What is this meant to be?
Are these even animals?
Crawls on its belly...?
Cymet! No!
We have to get them back... We have to!
Almet will be fine... She has to be...
Bugger me... I'm bloody beat...
Heh... Not as easy as hammerin' dents in kettles, ain't it?
R-Rowena!? What in the seventh hell─!?
Shush now. I've got a reputation to uphold.
Heh... Wouldn't have figured you the type for dressin' up like a rabbit.
Shut yer gob, Rowena! Ye look as bleedin' ridiculous as I do!
Anythin' for business...
After all, today's children are tomorrow's customers, I always say...
Ye greedy-arsed wench...
A happy Hatching–tide to you, my young friend!
You get an egg! And you get an egg!
Remember to shop at the House o' Splendors!
We're always lookin' for good help!
Here's yer bleedin' egg, ye whiny brat!
Take yer present an' stop yer bloody cryin' already!
Look! It's a talking rabbit!
Do you have an egg for me, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>Missus<Else/>Mister</If> Rabbit!?
Oh, thank you!
It's the best Hatching–tide ever!
Spriggy eggy! Eggy spriggy!
Spriggy givy! Spriggy taky!
I see...
I see we're not to have a peaceful journey.
We're getting close.
Mayhaps 'twas Bismarck with whom I ought have bargained...
Mayhaps 'twas Bismarck with whom I ought have bargained...
For heavens' sake...
This lot are nothing compared to the barnacles.
Such ease of motion despite his size─it's truly a wonder.
Look! A trench!
Such ease of motion despite his size─it's truly a wonder.
I'm certainly glad for Bismarck's preparation now.
Oof!
What a landing!
The force of it...'twas nigh overwhelming.
The force of it...'twas nigh overwhelming.
Just...stay on your feet this time, please.
Incredible!
Come along. Disturbing secrets await, and all that.
Our deepest gratitude, great one.
Our deepest gratitude, great one.
Thank you, Bismarck!
What is that?
We are fated to happen upon strange abominations, apparently.
What in the world...?
We are fated to happen upon strange abominations, apparently.
Never have I seen the like.
And it stinks. Lovely.
Might similar creatures dwell beneath the seas of the Source?
Do... Do you think there are more of them?
Some manner of harrowing, perhaps...?
Might similar creatures dwell beneath the seas of the Source?
Look at this architecture...
The similarities to Amaurot are undeniable.
'Tis unmistakably of the ancients' design.
Look at this architecture...
This is precisely what we were looking for.
What are they doing with that crystal?
Whatever they're doing, I doubt it's good for us.
In channeling aether through the crystal... Hmm.
In channeling aether through the crystal... Hmm.
I think we have passed the point of theory!
This is a reconstructed “concept” then?
Looks like the benthos have learned to use this place.
An impressive concept, to be certain.
An impressive concept, to be certain.
We might learn much, if more such crystals are to be found within.
There are so many...
Why, this... This could take a lifetime to study...
It's beautiful!
Why, this... This could take a lifetime to study...
There may be still more out of sight.
Though I mislike this, we may as well have done with it.
She plans to fight us herself? How efficient.
Yonder queen standeth as more than symbol to her soldiers. Have caution.
Though I mislike this, we may as well have done with it.
If she wants a fight, I'm happy to oblige!
For the sake of our world!
In the name of the Light!
To the ashes whence you came!
Death rain upon you!
I'll cut 'em down to size!
Lend me your strength, my servants!
Cleansing water, wash away evil!
Haaah!
I will destroy you!
Feel the pain!
There they are! Resting right out in the open!
Just as our scouts reported. We'll hit them hard and fast!
Like an eagle amongst the hares!
For Bozja!
Wh─ It's an ambush!
The bastards grow too bold by half...
Well? What are you waiting for? Crush them!
What's this I see? The pride of the Empire hard-pressed by Resistance rabble?
Bah, this brutish squabble has gone on long enough.
If you are so eager to feel the flames of war, then I shall be happy to oblige!
Hmph, you are more stalwart than I gave you credit for.
A poor showing from my own troops, but nevertheless...they served well enough to keep you distracted.
We will meet again, I think. In fact, I shall make certain of it.
A few more staves and we'd have had them... Retreat!
We'll never live this down...
Damn them!
Let the cowards flee. We need to lick our own wounds.
Even so, I'll count this one a victory!
That mage... What a nightmare.
We wouldn't have held out much longer.
Let's just be glad we survived...
Hmph. The briefest lick of fire, and they burn to cinders.
Why, this “Resistance” may as well be a stack of kindling!
Withdraw at your leisure, men. The enemy is beaten.
Right, pack it up, lads! We return the victors this day!
Haha! Glory to the IVth!
In Gabranth's name!
The imperials have us outmatched... Fall back!
We'll never win like this...
But...we had the upper hand!
They have us surrounded!
...We're done for.
Walked right into it...
Weapons at the ready! We fight our way free!
R-Right! We'll show these bastards!
Victory or death!
There will be no escape!
There will be no survivors!
Show them no mercy!
Charge!
\\<sigh> Once again I find our soldiers succumbing to an inferior force.
...Ah, but of course. I must stand before the vaunted “hero of the Resistance.”

Fear not, Albeleo.
I, Sartauvoir quo Soranus, will reduce this nuisance to ash.
Hah! Though I grow old and grey, ever does the thrill of battle stoke the embers of my soul!
Yes... The inferno builds to an all-consuming finale! Embrace the spectacle or perish!
Glorious! Simply glorious! You see how one must heed the words of one's elders?
...Even as a soldier must heed the commands of his general. I leave you now, but know that this contest will have its conclusion!
A pity. I had hoped for a more worthy contest.
Still, a soldier must fight as his general commands. We have not the luxury of choosing our opponents...
We're following, obviously.
More pods...
My kingdom for a proper bridge.
Odds on not having to fight that giant thing...?
Considering that's one of the androids that attacked us, low.
Hurry!
Careful!
This is odd...er than usual.
Did you see that blast radius!?
Three androids this time...
But still no 2P.
Excellent work on not dying!
This must be the way.
More falling!?
Whee!
Eurgh...
Look at all of this technology!
What is this place?
